g.text: Memory Layout Of an array in Java
Arrays of reference types in Java
- The variable persons resides in the stack
- The Array itself is created in the heap
- Initially, all elements in the array are null because no Person objects have been instantiated yet
- Memory addresses are added pointing to the actual Person objects in the Heap
- The uninitialized elements (persons[1]. persons[3], persons[4]) remain null
public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
Person[] persons = new Person[5]; // Stack: persons, Heap: [null, null, null, null, null]
// // Stack: persons, Heap: [ref1, null, null, null, null]: ref1: Person("Alice
// // // Stack: persons, Heap: [ref1, null, ref2, null, null]:
